('', 'Understanding PageFX', 'understanding-pagefx', '', '<p>This is probably one of Morph''s most powerful features, this is because it gives users the ability to set a wide variety of layout combination''s on any specific pages or components on their website. With Morph you can easily switch the left sidebar from 200px to 300px wide in a matter of seconds without touching any code.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p>There are a total of "8 left sidebar" and "5 right sidebar" width (banner friendly) and position variations available. These options can be combined with each other to create literally dozens of layout combination''s on any page and each page can be different. As with all other features in the FX Range, its super easy to set a layout for a page, there is nothing to configure, its just a matter of adding the required suffix or combined suffixes to the page in Joomla!... as easy as that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PageFX not only sets the sidebar layouts, there are some other things you can do as well. With Configurator you can also set the main website width based on 4 preset options (750px, 950px, 974px and 100%).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lastly, developers can also make use of the Page Class Suffix feature to add a custom “hook” to any page or pages on a website. This "hook" is set at the highest level in the page structure, this means any visual css can now be added or over ridden for that page only. This can be used to Brand specific areas of site, color code different sections to match a color coded navigation, set gallery pages to have a dark content background or add styling for a specific season like Christmas without modifying the actual code in any way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gone are the days where developing for Joomla! means that the layout of the template you are using will dictate your content.</p>', 1, @section_id, 0, @pfx_id, '2009-07-11 12:01:16', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-16 13:23:34', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 12:01:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title