('', 'Understanding ModuleFX', 'understanding-modulefx', '', '<p>If you have ever used one of our (JoomlaJunkie) templates before, you may recognize this feature, it is in fact the popularity of this feature in our 1st generation templates that sparked the birth of the entire FX Range of features available in Morph.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p>A suffix by definition in grammar is "a suffix (also postfix, ending) is an affix which is placed after the stem of a word"  In the Joomla world, a suffix refers to text added to the modules code. Every module in Joomla has a parameter option (input box) to add a suffix. What this does is "affix" the suffix to the default css class of the module in the modules code. This can then be used to add additional styling to a module or give it a different look from other modules on the page using css..</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ModuleFX in Morph, is the same as it was in our previous templates but its also a lot more advanced and usable than ever before, allowing users to literally modify the look of any module using a string of suffixes to combine dozens of background, header and icon styles to get create different front end appearances. Take a look at our <a href="http://modfx.joomlajunkie.com" target="_blank">ModuleFX Builder</a> that we created to help users of our 1st Generation templates build their module styles, this will give a good idea of how this feature works.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ModuleFX in Morph is a very long list of preset styles for the different elements of a module, ie. title or header and module container. More importantly most of these styles can be used in combination with each other to completely vary the effect. For example, a header icons can be applied with a heading color to create a module with a specific icon and color.... not fancy enough... what about adding the suffix or "rounded" and your module will automatically have round edges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is a list of the different types of styles that can be applied and combined together to get your website looking just how you want it without touching any of the code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module Body Background</h3>\r\n<p>Set different background colors, images, gradients and other effects to any module.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module Body font size and color</h3>\r\n<p>Set the module background font color and size.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Icons Styles</h3>\r\n<p>Apply different icons to the module headers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module Heading background</h3>\r\n<p>Set different background colors, images, gradients to module headers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module Heading text</h3>\r\n<p>Change the module headers font size, color and even transform the case of the letters.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Rounded</h3>\r\n<p>Convert your module with the above effects into a rounded corners module.</p>', 1, @section_id, 0, @modfx_id, '2009-07-11 12:05:19', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-16 13:00:52', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 12:05:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 5, 0, 1, '', '', 0, 1, 'robots=\nauthor='),
